<div><head>《繫辭上》</head>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.3" xml:lang="en">Heaven is exalted and Earth is humble,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.4" xml:lang="en">and Qian and Kun are defined.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.5" xml:lang="en">The humble and the high position in the hexagram having already been set out,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.6" xml:lang="en">and the noble and the base find their proper places.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.7" xml:lang="en">Action and inaction have their constant norm</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.8" xml:lang="en">and the hard and the pliable are determined.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.9" xml:lang="en">Methods group things according to (artificial) categories,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.10" xml:lang="en">and creatures divide up according to (natural) groups. See JZ Liu Hui 1.9</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.11" xml:lang="en">[And as a result of all this] good fortune and misfortune arise.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.12" xml:lang="en">In [the realm of] Heaven these bring about symbolic images,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.13" xml:lang="en">and in [the realm of] Earth they bring about [concrete physical] forms,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.14" xml:lang="en">so change and transformation manifest themselves. [1132]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.15" xml:lang="en">And so:</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.16" xml:lang="en">The hard and soft stroke each other,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.17" xml:lang="en">the eight trigrams activate each other. [1133]</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.18" xml:lang="en">They urge things on with claps of thunder,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.19" xml:lang="en">they moisten them with thunderstorms,/</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.20" xml:lang="en">Sun and moon take their regular paths,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.21" xml:lang="en">and at one time it is cold, at another it is hot./ [1134]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.22" xml:lang="en">The Way of Qian gives complete form to the male,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.23" xml:lang="en">the Way of Kun gives complete form to the female. [1135]</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.24" xml:lang="en">Qian oversees the Great Beginning,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.25" xml:lang="en">and Kun is activated/activates itself to form things. [1136]</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.26" xml:lang="en">Qian oversees things through natural ease,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.27" xml:lang="en">and Kun is capableof things through natural simplicity. [1137]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.28" xml:lang="en">If something is possessed of natural ease, it is easy to understand;</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.29" xml:lang="en">and if something is possessed of natural simplicity, it is easy to follow.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.30" xml:lang="en">If something is easy to understand, it will have intimate allies,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.31" xml:lang="en">and if something is easy to follow, it will have manifest effects;</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.32" xml:lang="en">if something has intimate allies then it can be made to last,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.33" xml:lang="en">and if something has manifest effects it can be made to be great.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.34" xml:lang="en">The capacity to be made to last, that is the inner power of the man of worth.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.35" xml:lang="en">the capacity to be made to be great, that is the main purpose of the man of worth [1138]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.36" xml:lang="en">As Qián and Kùn] being possessed of natural ease and natural simplicity</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.37" xml:lang="en">the principles of All under Heaven are (got&gt;) put in place.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.38" xml:lang="en">As the principles of All under Heaven are put in place [1139]</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-1a.39" xml:lang="en">they give complete form to the space/position between them.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.2" xml:lang="en">The sages</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.3" xml:lang="en">set up the [concrete] hexagrams</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.4" xml:lang="en">and [thus] and thus systematically observed the abstract images;</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.5" xml:lang="en">They appended the Statements</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.6" xml:lang="en">and thus clarified the auspiciousness/inauspiciousness (which they imply). [1140]</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.7" xml:lang="en">The hard and the soft lines push each other along</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.8" xml:lang="en">so that they produce change and transformation. [1141]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.9" xml:lang="en">Therefore,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.10" xml:lang="en">the auspicious and the inauspicious lines</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.11" xml:lang="en">are abstract images [respectively] of failure or success;</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.12" xml:lang="en">[Lines indicating] regret or remorse</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.13" xml:lang="en">are abstract images of objects of worry and concern. [1142]</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.14" xml:lang="en">Change and transformation</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.15" xml:lang="en">are abstract images of advance and withdrawal;</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.16" xml:lang="en">The strong and the weak</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.17" xml:lang="en">are images of day and night.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.18" xml:lang="en">The movement of the six hexagram lines</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.19" xml:lang="en">embodies the Dao of the three ultimates [Heaven, Earth and Man]. [1143]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.20" xml:lang="en">Therefore,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.21" xml:lang="en">as for the superior man</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.22" xml:lang="en">the [abstract] place in which he dwells and feels secure</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.23" xml:lang="en">is the sequential order of the Changes;</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.24" xml:lang="en">What he playfully ponders with deep joy</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.25" xml:lang="en">are the statements belonging to the hexagram lines. [1144]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.26" xml:lang="en">Therefore,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.27" xml:lang="en">as for the superior man,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.28" xml:lang="en">when remaining still, systematically observes the relevant abstract images,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.29" xml:lang="en">and he playfully ponders on the relevant statements;</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.30" xml:lang="en">when engaging in [deliberate] action, he systematically observes the line changes</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.31" xml:lang="en">and he playfully ponders on the relevant prognostications.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.32" xml:lang="en">And so:</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.33" xml:lang="en">"Since Heaven succours him,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-2a.34" xml:lang="en">things turn out auspicious [for him] and nothing fails to be to his advantage." [1145]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.2" xml:lang="en">Therefore:</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.3" xml:lang="en">The ranking of noble versus base</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.4" xml:lang="en">depends on the positions of the lines in the hexagram.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.5" xml:lang="en">The adjustment to pettiness or greatness [1146]</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.6" xml:lang="en">are the elements that will pronounce on the abstract images;</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.7" xml:lang="en">The differentiation between the auspicious and the inauspicious</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.8" xml:lang="en">pronounce on relevant failure or success;</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.9" xml:lang="en">the concepts of remorse and regret</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.10" xml:lang="en">pronounce on minor blemishes.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.11" xml:lang="en">One who has no blame attached</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.12" xml:lang="en">is in a good position to make up for transgressions. [1147]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.16" xml:lang="en">depends on the statements. [1148]</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.17" xml:lang="en">Worry about objects of remorse or regret</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.18" xml:lang="en">depends on the illustrations.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.19" xml:lang="en">Saving those who (suffer misfortune but are) "without blame"</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.20" xml:lang="en">depends on regret. [1149]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.21" xml:lang="en">Therefore:</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.22" xml:lang="en">In the hexagrams reside pettiness versus greatness.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.23" xml:lang="en">In the statements reside peril versus easy prospects.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.24" xml:lang="en">As for the statements in general,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.25" xml:lang="en">these, in each case. indicate where things are going. [1150]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.26" xml:lang="en">The Changes fits perfectly with Heaven and Earth.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.27" xml:lang="en">Thus it is able to fill out and pull togoether the Way of Heaven and Earth.[1151]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.28" xml:lang="en">Above we use [the Changes] to systematically observe the configurations of Heaven,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.29" xml:lang="en">and below we use it to examine precisely the patterns of Earth.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.30" xml:lang="en">Therefore one understands the reasons behind what is hidden and what is clear,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.31" xml:lang="en">One traces the beginnings</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.32" xml:lang="en">and then reverts to the outcomes.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-3a.33" xml:lang="en">As a result one understands the explanation of death and life.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.2" xml:lang="en">The subtle vital energy produces things,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.3" xml:lang="en">and the floating spirit produces change [in things].</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.4" xml:lang="en">Therefore one understands the true state of gods and spirits. [1152]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.5" xml:lang="en">It (Changes? Way? One) is patterned on Heaven and Earth,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.6" xml:lang="en">therefore one does not go against them.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.7" xml:lang="en">One's understanding pervades the myriad things</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.8" xml:lang="en">and [thus] guides along and helps along All under Heaven,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.9" xml:lang="en">therefore one makes no inadvertent mistakes.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.10" xml:lang="en">One is expansive in many directions</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.11" xml:lang="en">but does drift along;</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.12" xml:lang="en">one rejoices in Heaven,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.13" xml:lang="en">understands fate.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.14" xml:lang="en">Therefore one does not worry.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.15" xml:lang="en">It brings peace to the lands</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.16" xml:lang="en">and is generous in its Goodness;</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.17" xml:lang="en">Therefore it can show loving care. [1153]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.18" xml:lang="en">Comprehensively one comprehensively encompasses the transformation of Heaven and Earth</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.19" xml:lang="en">and does not make inadvertent mistakes.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.20" xml:lang="en">Indirectly one causes the myriad things to gain their complete shape</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.21" xml:lang="en">and makes no omssions [in this].</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.22" xml:lang="en">One has a thorough grasp of the Way that governs day and night</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.23" xml:lang="en">and one is wise.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.24" xml:lang="en">Thus the supernatural occupies no physical space,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.25" xml:lang="en">and the changes have no physical substance. [1154]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.26" xml:lang="en">The succession of Yin and Yang is called the Way. [1155]</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.27" xml:lang="en">That which continues on along these lines of the Way is good.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.28" xml:lang="en">That which completes the Way is inherent nature. [1156]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.29" xml:lang="en">When the benevolent see it they call it benevolence,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.30" xml:lang="en">and when the competent see it they call it int elligence.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.31" xml:lang="en">The Hundred Families use it daily but do not understand it.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-4a.32" xml:lang="en">Therefore the Way of a superior man is something seldom found! [1157]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.2" xml:lang="en">One manifests it in benevolent action</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.3" xml:lang="en">and one hides it in its application.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.4" xml:lang="en">It eggs on the myriad things</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.5" xml:lang="en">and does not share the anxieties of the sages.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.6" xml:lang="en">How perfect is rich inner power and its great asset![1158]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.7" xml:lang="en">It's superabundance is called "great asset".</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.8" xml:lang="en">It's daily self-renewal one calls "abundant inner power". [1159]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.9" xml:lang="en">In its capacity to produce and reproduce we call it "change".</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.10" xml:lang="en">Insofar as it gives full form to abstract images, we call it Qián.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.11" xml:lang="en">Insofar as it imitates these patterns [set by the abstract images], we call it Kūn. [1161]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.12" xml:lang="en">Masterig the technique so as to understand the future is called 'prognostication',</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.13" xml:lang="en">being in tune with the changes is called 'conduct of business' [1162]</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.14" xml:lang="en">What from the Yin and the Yang one cannot fathom is called 'the supernatural.' [1163]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.15" xml:lang="en">As for the Changes,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.16" xml:lang="en">they are great!</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.17" xml:lang="en">If one keeps explaining them as something distant,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.18" xml:lang="en">then there is no stopping them.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.19" xml:lang="en">If one keeps explaining them as something near,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.20" xml:lang="en">then they are at rest and straight.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.21" xml:lang="en">If one keeps explaining them as something between Heaven and Earth,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.22" xml:lang="en">then they are all complete. [1164]</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.23" xml:lang="en">As for Qian,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.24" xml:lang="en">when at rest it is concentrated,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.25" xml:lang="en">when avtive it moves along a straight line:</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.26" xml:lang="en">this is how its greatness emerges from it.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.27" xml:lang="en">As for Kun,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.28" xml:lang="en">when at rest it is in condensed harmony,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.29" xml:lang="en">when active it is expansive:</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR1a0001_tls_065-5a.30" xml:lang="en">this is how its vastness emerges. [1165]</seg>
</p>
